lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, June 2 -- Ambassador Winant, who arrived here tonight by airplane from New York after flying from Europe by clipper, has come home at his own request to make personal reports to President Roosevelt and Secretary Hull, it was said at the State Department today.
abstract: Winant arrives, Wash; Hull-Roosevelt telephone conf; State Dept denies Winant brought new Brit peace plea
